      • getEntities2Delete

        protected static <ID,E extends net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.GenericEntity<ID>> List<E> getEntities2Delete(Collection<E> currentEntities,
                                                                                     Collection<E> entitiesToSave)
        Determines the entities to delete if currentList is the current list from the persistence and listToSave is the new list that shall be saved. In other words this method selects the entities from currentList that are not contained in listToSave.
        Type Parameters:
        ID - is the generic type of the ID.
        E - is the generic type of the entity.
        Parameters:
        currentEntities - is the Collection of the entities currently persisted. We assume that all objects in this list have an ID value (that is not null).
        entitiesToSave - is the Collection that contains the entities that shall be saved. It may contain entities that have no ID that shall be newly created.
        Returns:
        the List with the entities to delete.
